"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Store Stripped Transcripts in MySQL\n\n## Context\n\nThe transcript pipeline has a GitHub API bottleneck. Today, transcripts (`full.jsonl`) are fetched from GitHub in three places:\n1. **Search indexing** (`processSearchIndexBatch`) — fetches per-checkpoint via REST on every index\n2. **Transcript endpoint** (`/checkpoints/:id/transcript`) — fetches from GitHub on KV cache miss (first user click)\n3. **Backfills** — repo sync discovers checkpoints but never fetches transcripts; search indexing does it later\n\nBy storing stripped transcripts in MySQL at webhook time, all downstream consumers (search, UI, backfill) read from the DB. GitHub API calls for transcripts drop to zero after initial ingest.\n\nThe Python `strip-transcript.py` script reduces JSONL by ~60-80% by keeping only fields the parsers actually read — making DB storage practical.\n\n## Architecture Decision: No New Queue\n\nWe already have `SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE`. Today it: fetches checkpoints from DB → fetches transcripts from GitHub → indexes to Turbopuffer. The change: fetch transcript from GitHub → strip → store in DB → index to Turbopuffer (using DB transcript). Same queue, same trigger points, just adds a DB write step. No new queue needed.\n\nFor backfill of newly connected repos, `repo-sync-service` already queues to `SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE` — we just need to make sure it does so consistently. The search index queue handler becomes the single place where transcripts are fetched from GitHub and stored.\n\n## Schema: New Column on `repo_checkpoints`\n\n**Why not a separate table?** The transcript is 1:1 with a checkpoint. A separate table adds JOIN complexity and a second upsert in every write path. A LONGTEXT column on the existing table keeps things simple. MySQL stores LONGTEXT off-page, so it doesn't affect queries that don't SELECT it. We just need to avoid `SELECT *` in hot paths (already the case — all queries use explicit column lists).\n\n**Storage format: per-session JSON map.** Multi-session checkpoints store each session's stripped JSONL separately, matching the GitHub folder structure:\n```json\n{\"0\": \"...stripped session 0 jsonl...\", \"1\": \"...stripped session 1 jsonl...\"}\n```\nThis makes it easy to serve individual sessions and matches the `0/full.jsonl`, `1/full.jsonl` structure on GitHub.\n\n## Changes\n\n### 1. DB Migration: Add `transcript_stripped` column\n\n**New file: `api/db/migrations/004_add_transcript_stripped.ts`**\n\n```sql\nALTER TABLE repo_checkpoints ADD COLUMN transcript_stripped JSON;\n```\n\nUsing Kysely migration pattern (see `003_index_users_github_login.ts`). JSON column stores per-session map `{\"0\": \"...\", \"1\": \"...\"}`. MySQL JSON supports up to 1GB — stripped transcripts are typically 50-200KB total.\n\n**Update: `api/db/types.ts`** — add `transcript_stripped: string | null` to generated types.\n\n**Update: `api/src/lib/db/checkpoints.ts`** — add `transcript_stripped: string | null` to `RepoCheckpoint` interface.\n\n### 2. TypeScript `stripTranscript()` function\n\n**New file: `api/src/lib/strip-transcript.ts`**\n\nPort of `strip-transcript.py`. Core function:\n\n```typescript\nexport function stripTranscript(jsonlContent: string): string\n```\n\n- Processes line-by-line (no full parse into memory)\n- Drops entry types: `progress`, `file-history-snapshot`, `queue-operation`, `system`\n- For `assistant`: keeps `type`, `timestamp`, `message.id`, `message.content` (drops thinking blocks, tool_use `caller`)\n- For `user` tool_result: keeps `type`, `content[].tool_use_id`, `toolUseResult.{type,file,error,answers}`\n- For `user` text: keeps `type`, `timestamp`, `uuid`, `message.content`\n- Returns JSONL string (newline-separated)\n- Agent-agnostic: the stripping targets the common JSONL superset. Non-Claude agents that use different entry types just pass through user/assistant entries\n\n**New file: `api/src/lib/strip-transcript.test.ts`** — unit tests verifying:\n- Thinking blocks dropped\n- Progress/system entries dropped\n- Tool use caller stripped\n- User text entries preserved\n- Tool result entries minimized\n- Round-trip: stripped JSONL still parses correctly via `ClaudeCodeParser`\n- Empty/malformed input handled\n\n### 3. Search Index Queue: Fetch → Strip → Store → Index\n\n**Modify: `api/src/lib/search-index-queue.ts`**\n\nChange `processSearchIndexBatch` flow:\n\n```\nCurrent:  DB(checkpoints) → GitHub(transcript) → parse → Turbopuffer\nNew:      DB(checkpoints) → check DB(transcript_stripped) →\n            if missing: GitHub(full.jsonl) → strip → store in DB →\n          parse stripped transcript → Turbopuffer\n```\n\nConcrete changes:\n- After fetching checkpoints from DB, check which ones already have `transcript_stripped` populated\n- For those missing transcripts: fetch from GitHub, call `stripTranscript()`, upsert to `repo_checkpoints.transcript_stripped`\n- For Turbopuffer indexing: parse the stripped transcript (same `getParserForAgent` + excerpt extraction as today)\n- Need to add `transcript_stripped` to the `getByIds` query in the checkpoints DB layer\n\n**Modify: `api/src/lib/planetscale/checkpoints.ts`**\n\nAdd a method to update transcript_stripped:\n\n```typescript\nasync updateTranscriptBatch(\n  repoId: string,\n  updates: Array<{ checkpoint_id: string; transcript_stripped: string }>\n): Promise<number>\n```\n\nAlso update `getByIds` to include `transcript_stripped` in the SELECT when a flag requests it (to avoid loading large text by default).\n\n### 4. Transcript Endpoint: DB-First with GitHub Fallback\n\n**Modify: `api/src/routes/cache.ts`** (transcript endpoint, ~line 2585)\n\nNew flow:\n```\nRequest → KV cache hit? → return cached\n        → DB has transcript_stripped? → parse + return (+ cache to KV)\n        → GitHub fallback (existing code) → return (+ cache to KV)\n```\n\nThe DB lookup is a simple query: get `transcript_stripped` and `sessions` JSON from `repo_checkpoints` where `checkpoint_id = ?`. The `sessions` column already has per-session metadata (agent, sessionId, tokenUsage, attribution, transcriptIdentifierAtStart).\n\nFor multi-session checkpoints: the `transcript_stripped` JSON column contains `{\"0\": \"...jsonl...\", \"1\": \"...jsonl...\"}`. The `sessions` JSON column has per-session metadata (agent, sessionId, tokenUsage, attribution, transcriptIdentifierAtStart). The transcript endpoint iterates sessions, pulls the JSONL for each index from the map, and parses with the appropriate agent parser — same as today's GitHub fetch loop but from a single DB read.\n\n**Important**: The stripped transcript preserves all fields the parsers read, so existing parsing code works unchanged.\n\n### 5. Backfill: Repo Sync → Search Index Queue\n\n**Modify: `api/src/lib/repo-sync-service.ts`**\n\nAfter `syncRepoCheckpoints` finishes upserting checkpoints, queue discovered checkpoint IDs to `SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE`:\n\n```typescript\n// After successful sync, queue for transcript storage + search indexing\nif (checkpointIds.length > 0 && env.SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE) {\n  for (let i = 0; i < checkpointIds.length; i += 50) {\n    await env.SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE.send({\n      repoId,\n      checkpointIds: checkpointIds.slice(i, i + 50),\n      queuedAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n    });\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Modify: `api/src/lib/repo-sync-queue.ts`**\n\nPass `env` to `syncRepoCheckpoints` (or pass the queue directly) so it can enqueue. Currently the sync result is returned to the queue consumer which has access to `env` — so the queuing can happen in the consumer after sync completes.\n\nAdd to `RepoSyncResult`:\n```typescript\ndiscoveredCheckpointIds?: string[];\n```\n\nReturn this from `syncRepoCheckpoints`, then in the queue consumer (`processRepoSyncBatch`), queue to SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE after successful sync.\n\n### 6. Wire DB Types\n\n**Modify: `api/src/lib/db/checkpoints.ts`**\n- Add `transcript_stripped: string | null` to `RepoCheckpoint`\n- Add `transcript_stripped?: string | null` to `CheckpointWithCommit` (optional — only populated when requested)\n\n**Modify: `api/src/lib/db/db-types.ts`**\n- Add `getTranscript(repoId: string, checkpointId: string): Promise<{ transcript_stripped: string | null; sessions: Json | null } | null>` to `CheckpointsNamespace`\n- Add `updateTranscriptBatch(...)` to `CheckpointsNamespace`\n\n## Files Modified\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `api/db/migrations/004_add_transcript_stripped.ts` | **New** — migration adding LONGTEXT column |\n| `api/db/types.ts` | Add `transcript_stripped` to generated types |\n| `api/src/lib/strip-transcript.ts` | **New** — TypeScript port of strip-transcript.py |\n| `api/src/lib/strip-transcript.test.ts` | **New** — unit tests for stripping |\n| `api/src/lib/search-index-queue.ts` | Fetch → strip → store in DB → index flow |\n| `api/src/lib/db/checkpoints.ts` | Add transcript field to types |\n| `api/src/lib/db/db-types.ts` | Add transcript methods to CheckpointsNamespace |\n| `api/src/lib/planetscale/checkpoints.ts` | Implement updateTranscriptBatch + getTranscript |\n| `api/src/routes/cache.ts` | Transcript endpoint: DB-first lookup |\n| `api/src/lib/repo-sync-service.ts` | Return discoveredCheckpointIds in result |\n| `api/src/lib/repo-sync-queue.ts` | Queue to SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE after sync |\n\n## Verification\n\n1. `npx tsx scripts/migrate.ts` — run migration against local MySQL\n2. `npx vitest run` — strip-transcript tests pass + existing tests pass\n3. `npx tsc --noEmit` — type check\n4. Manual: trigger a webhook push → verify `transcript_stripped` populated in DB\n5. Manual: hit transcript endpoint → verify it reads from DB (no GitHub call in logs)\n6. Manual: search a checkpoint → verify transcript content appears in search results\n7. Manual: connect a new repo → verify backfill queues search indexing → transcripts stored\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read th